description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Directorate are looking to appoint an enthusiastic and suitably qualified Receptionist/Administration Officer who will support the AECU service, working on part time basis of 20.75hrs hours per week, on a permanent basis. This will predominantly be working evening hours but the successful candidate would need to be flexible to meet the needs of the service as day time hours maybe necessary.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The main purpose of this post will be to provide a comprehensive and confidential clerical and receptionist support in relation to emergency attendances and admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide a full reception service to patients, visitors and staff, co-ordinating and booking appointments, ensuring all patients are booked, transferred, admitted and discharged correctly throughout their journey in the AECU Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be trained to use WPAS (Myrddin) to input and extract data, and undertake a full range of clerical duties to ensure the smooth running of the whole of the AECU Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An understanding of customer care and meeting the needs of the general public is necessary for this position, therefore an excellent telephone and communication manner will need to be demonstrated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dawn Daniel, Administration Manager&lt;br /&gt;dawn.daniel@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01443 443443 ex 74877&lt;/p&gt;
